#Load the database Import the pSERG database into R

pSERG <- read.csv('C:\\Users\\crist\\Desktop\\pSERG_DOSING.csv')

##Clean the database and transform variables Keep only the population of interest and transform variables for analysis.

# Transform date of status epilepticus onset into date format
pSERG$DATESEIZURE <- as.Date(pSERG$DATESEIZURE, format = "%m/%d/%Y")

# Keep only patients from 2014 onwards (start of controls collection: September 2014)
pSERG = subset(pSERG, DATESEIZURE >= "2014-09-01")
dim(pSERG)
## [1]  560 1582
# Order by patient and then by date of status epilepticus
pSERG <- pSERG[order(pSERG$PATIENT_LABEL, pSERG$DATESEIZURE), ]
dim(pSERG)
## [1]  560 1582
# Delete duplicate episodes from the same patient
pSERG <- pSERG[!duplicated(pSERG$PATIENT_LABEL), ]
dim(pSERG)
## [1]  478 1582
# Delete patients with unknown group of SE (refractory or control)
pSERG <- pSERG[which(pSERG$SE_GROUP == "refractory_case" | pSERG$SE_GROUP == "control_case"), ]
dim(pSERG)
## [1]  478 1582
#Create a variable for refractory SE group
pSERG$RSE <- ifelse(pSERG$SE_GROUP == "refractory_case", 1, 0)

# Transform age into numeric
pSERG$G_T_STTS_PLPTCUS_EPISODE_YEARS <- as.numeric(as.character(pSERG$G_T_STTS_PLPTCUS_EPISODE_YEARS))
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion
pSERG$G_T_STTS_PLPTCS_EPISODE_MONTHS <- as.numeric(as.character(pSERG$G_T_STTS_PLPTCS_EPISODE_MONTHS))
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion
# Transform age into a single variable with age in years
pSERG$ageyears <- pSERG$G_T_STTS_PLPTCUS_EPISODE_YEARS + (pSERG$G_T_STTS_PLPTCS_EPISODE_MONTHS / 12)

# Delete patients with unknown age
pSERG <- pSERG[complete.cases(pSERG[ , "ageyears"]), ]
dim(pSERG)
## [1]  468 1584
# Delete patients with unknown sex
pSERG <- pSERG[which(pSERG$SEX == "male" | pSERG$SEX == "female"), ]
CrossTable(pSERG$SEX)
##

dim(pSERG)
## [1]  468 1584
#Create variable male sex
pSERG$male <- ifelse(pSERG$SEX=="male",1,0)

#Transform weight units into kg
pSERG <- pSERG[which(pSERG$WEIGHTUNITS == "kg" | pSERG$WEIGHTUNITS == "lbs"), ]
pSERG$WEIGHT <- as.numeric(as.character(pSERG$WEIGHT))
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion
pSERG$WEIGHT <- ifelse(pSERG$WEIGHTUNITS == "kg", pSERG$WEIGHT, pSERG$WEIGHT * 2.2)

# Delete patients with unknown hospital onset
pSERG <- pSERG[which(pSERG$HOSPITALONSET == "yes" | pSERG$HOSPITALONSET == "no"), ]
dim(pSERG)
## [1]  468 1585
# Create variable white race (vs non-white)
pSERG$white <- ifelse(pSERG$RACE == "white", 1, 0)

# Create variable not hispanic ethnicity (vs hispanic)
pSERG$nothispanic <- ifelse(pSERG$ETHNICITY == "not_hispanic_or_latino", 1, 0)

# Create variable history of developmental delay
pSERG$delay[grepl("delay", pSERG$PAST)] <- 1
pSERG$delay[!grepl("delay", pSERG$PAST)] <- 0

# Create variable history of cerebral palsy
pSERG$palsy[grepl("palsy", pSERG$PAST)] <- 1
pSERG$palsy[!grepl("palsy", pSERG$PAST)] <- 0

# Create variable febrile
pSERG$febrile[grepl("febrile", pSERG$PAST)] <- 1
pSERG$febrile[!grepl("febrile", pSERG$PAST)] <- 0

# Create variable no history of epilepsy
pSERG$NOepilepsy[grepl("epi", pSERG$PAST)] <- 0
pSERG$NOepilepsy[!grepl("epi", pSERG$PAST)] <- 1

# Create variable history of epilepsy
pSERG$priorepilepsy[grepl("epi", pSERG$PAST)] <- 1
pSERG$priorepilepsy[!grepl("epi", pSERG$PAST)] <- 0

# Create variable history of status epilepticus
pSERG$priorSE[grepl("status", pSERG$PAST)] <- 1
pSERG$priorSE[!grepl("status", pSERG$PAST)] <- 0

# Create variable no prior neurological history
pSERG$none[grepl("none", pSERG$PAST)] <- 1
pSERG$none[!grepl("none", pSERG$PAST)] <- 0

#Delete patients with etiology not available
pSERG <- pSERG[complete.cases(pSERG[ ,"ETIOLOGY"]), ]
dim(pSERG)
## [1]  468 1594
#Create variable for structural etiology
pSERG$STRUCTURALETIOLOGY<- ifelse(grepl("structural", pSERG$ETIOLOGY) == TRUE, 1, 0)

#Create variable for unknown etiology
pSERG$UNKETIOLOGY<- ifelse(grepl("unknown", pSERG$ETIOLOGY) == TRUE, 1, 0)

#Create variable for genetic etiology
pSERG$GENETICETIOLOGY <- ifelse(grepl("genetic", pSERG$ETIOLOGY) == TRUE, 1, 0)

#Create variable for metabolic etiology
pSERG$METABOLICETIOLOGY <- ifelse(grepl("metabolic", pSERG$ETIOLOGY) == TRUE, 1, 0)

#Create variable for other etiology
pSERG$OTHERETIOLOGY <- ifelse(grepl("other", pSERG$ETIOLOGY) == TRUE, 1, 0)

#Create variable for febrile cause
pSERG$Febrile_cause <- 0
pSERG$Febrile_cause <- ifelse(pSERG$CAUSE == "febrile_status_epilepticus", 1, 0)

#Create a variable for prior home medication (when home medication can be used as 2nd line)
CrossTable(pSERG$HOMEMED.0)

### Create a variable for intermittent SE
pSERG$INTERMITTENT <- ifelse(grepl("intermittent",pSERG$TYPESTATUS) == TRUE, 1, 0)

#Create variable for inhospital BZD administration 
pSERG$INHOSPITAL <- ifelse(pSERG$BZDLOCATION.0 =="studyh"|pSERG$BZDLOCATION.0 =="outsideh", 1, 0)
CrossTable(pSERG$INHOSPITAL)

#Create a variable for patients who received continuous infusion
pSERG$CONTINF <-ifelse(pSERG$CONTMED.0=="",0,1)

# Transform convulsive duration into numeric
pSERG$CONVULSIVEDURATION <- as.numeric(as.character(pSERG$CONVULSIVEDURATION))
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion
# Create convulsive duration in minutes
pSERG$convulsivemin <- pSERG$CONVULSIVEDURATION
pSERG$convulsivehr <- pSERG$CONVULSIVEDURATION * 60
pSERG$convulsivedurationmin <- ifelse(pSERG$CONVULSIVEDURATIONUNITS == "min", pSERG$convulsivemin, pSERG$convulsivehr)

# Create a variable for Seizure duration in hours
pSERG$SEIZUREDURATION <- as.numeric(as.character(pSERG$SEIZUREDURATION))
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion
for (i in 1 : dim(pSERG)[1]) {
  if (pSERG$SEIZUREDURATIONUNITS[i] == "day") {
    pSERG$SEIZUREDURATION[i] = pSERG$SEIZUREDURATION[i] * 1440
  } else if (pSERG$SEIZUREDURATIONUNITS[i] == "min") {
    pSERG$SEIZUREDURATION[i] = pSERG$SEIZUREDURATION[i]
  } else if (pSERG$SEIZUREDURATIONUNITS[i] == "hr") {
    pSERG$SEIZUREDURATION[i] = pSERG$SEIZUREDURATION[i] * 60
  }
}

pSERG$SEIZUREDURATIONHR <- pSERG$SEIZUREDURATION/60

#Create a variable for ICU days
pSERG$ICU_DURATION <- as.numeric(as.character(pSERG$ICU_DURATION))
## Warning: NAs introduced by coercion
pSERG$ICU_DURATION <- ifelse(pSERG$ICU_DURATION ==0.00000,NA,pSERG$ICU_DURATION)
pSERG$ICU_DURATIONdays<- ifelse(pSERG$ICU_UNITS=="days",pSERG$ICU_DURATION,pSERG$ICU_DURATION/24)

#Create variable requirement for intubation excluding unknown values
pSERG$intubation[pSERG$INTUBATION == "yes"] <- 1
pSERG$intubation[pSERG$INTUBATION == "no"] <- 0
CrossTable(pSERG$intubation)

##    Cell Contents

#Create variables for the type of BZD received
#Identify number of patients who received lorazepam as first single BZD
pSERG$FIRSTLZP<-ifelse(pSERG$BZDMED.0 == "lorazepam",1,0)

#Identify number of patients who received diazepam as first single BZD
pSERG$FIRSTDZP<-ifelse(pSERG$BZDMED.0 == "diazepam",1,0)

#Identify number of patients who received midazolam as first single BZD
pSERG$FIRSTMDZ<-ifelse(pSERG$BZDMED.0 == "midazolam",1,0)

#Identify number of patients who received clonazepam as first single BZD
pSERG$FIRSTCLZ<-ifelse(pSERG$BZDMEDOTHER.0 == "Clonazepam"|pSERG$BZDMEDOTHER.0 == "clonazepam "|pSERG$BZDMEDOTHER.0 == "Clonazepam Wafer"|pSERG$BZDMEDOTHER.0 == "clonazepam",1,0)

#Identify number of patients that received Clobazam as first single BZD 
pSERG$FIRSTCLBZ<-ifelse(pSERG$BZDMEDOTHER.0 == "Clobazam",1,0)

#Identify the dose administered as initial BZD dose LORAZEPAM

##Initial single dose of lorazepam
#Weight-based dose (<40kg)
nobs(pSERG[which(pSERG$FIRSTLZP==1 & pSERG$WEIGHT < 40), ]$BZDDOSE.0KG)

#TOTAL BZD DOSE Total BZD Dose within 10 minutes of treatment initiation

###Lorazepam

#Number of LZP administered within 10 minutes of treatment initiation regardless of the BZD type
pSERG$BZDTIMEDELTA.1<- pSERG$BZDTIME.1-pSERG$BZDTIME.0
pSERG$BZDTIMEDELTA.2<- pSERG$BZDTIME.2-pSERG$BZDTIME.0
pSERG$BZDTIMEDELTA.3<- pSERG$BZDTIME.3-pSERG$BZDTIME.0
pSERG$BZDTIMEDELTA.4<- pSERG$BZDTIME.4-pSERG$BZDTIME.0

for(i in 1: dim(pSERG) [1]){
pSERG$LZPnumber[i] <- 0
if ( !is.na(pSERG$BZDTIMEDELTA.1[i]) & pSERG$BZDMED.1[i]=="lorazepam" & pSERG$BZDTIMEDELTA.1[i]<=10) {
pSERG$LZPnumber[i]<-pSERG$LZPnumber[i]+1 }
if  (!is.na(pSERG$BZDTIMEDELTA.2[i]) & pSERG$BZDMED.2[i]=="lorazepam" & pSERG$BZDTIMEDELTA.2[i]<=10){
pSERG$LZPnumber[i]<-pSERG$LZPnumber[i]+1}
if ( !is.na(pSERG$BZDTIMEDELTA.3[i]) & pSERG$BZDMED.3[i]=="lorazepam" & pSERG$BZDTIMEDELTA.3[i]<=10){
pSERG$LZPnumber[i]<-pSERG$LZPnumber[i]+1}
if (!is.na(pSERG$BZDTIMEDELTA.4[i]) & pSERG$BZDMED.4[i]=="lorazepam" & pSERG$BZDTIMEDELTA.4[i]<=10){
pSERG$LZPnumber[i]<-pSERG$LZPnumber[i]+1}

}

pSERG$LZPnumber <- ifelse(pSERG$BZDMED.0=="lorazepam", pSERG$LZPnumber + 1, pSERG$LZPnumber)
CrossTable(pSERG$LZPnumber)

for(i in 1: dim(pSERG) [1]){

#Primary outcome (RSE)

#Univariate analysis comparing clinical and demographic characteristics between RSE vs. non-RSE groups

##Demographic and clinical variables

#Age
wilcox.test(pSERG$ageyears ~ pSERG$RSE)
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  pSERG$ageyears by pSERG$RSE
## W = 12822, p-value = 0.931
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
#Time to first BZD
wilcox.test(pSERG$BZDTIME.0 ~ pSERG$RSE)
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  pSERG$BZDTIME.0 by pSERG$RSE
## W = 12792, p-value = 0.9594
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
#Time to first non-BZD ASM
wilcox.test(pSERG$AEDTIME.0 ~ pSERG$RSE)
## 
##  Wilcoxon rank sum test with continuity correction
## 
## data:  pSERG$AEDTIME.0 by pSERG$RSE
## W = 13009, p-value = 0.7543
## alternative hypothesis: true location shift is not equal to 0
#Categorical predictors (Chi2)
#sex
tblmale=table(pSERG$male,pSERG$RSE)
chisq.test(tblmale)
## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test with Yates' continuity correction
## 
## data:  tblmale
## X-squared = 0.33994, df = 1, p-value = 0.5599
#Race (white)
tblwhite=table(pSERG$white,pSERG$RSE)
chisq.test(tblwhite)
## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test with Yates' continuity correction
## 
## data:  tblwhite
## X-squared = 1.5877, df = 1, p-value = 0.2077
#Ethnicity
tblnothispanic=table(pSERG$nothispanic,pSERG$RSE)
chisq.test(tblnothispanic)
## 
##  Pearson's Chi-squared test with Yates' continuity correction
## 
## data:  tblnothispanic
## X-squared = 1.103, df = 1, p-value = 0.2936

tblnone=table(pSERG$none,pSERG$RSE)

#Bar graph low BZD dose and RSE

#Transform variable low BZD dose into factor
class(pSERG$BZDlow10)
## [1] "numeric"
pSERG$BZDlow10 <- as.factor(as.numeric(pSERG$BZDlow10))
class(pSERG$BZDlow10)
## [1] "factor"
#Transform value into percentages
percent_RSE <- pSERG %>%
    count(SE_GROUP, BZDlow10) %>%
    group_by(BZDlow10) %>%
    mutate(percent = (n / sum(n)) * 100) %>%
    ungroup()

#Create bar graph comparing BZD dose between subgroups
percent_RSE %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = SE_GROUP, y = percent, fill = BZDlow10)) +
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge", width = 0.6) +
    theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 12, color = "black", face = "bold"),
          axis.title = element_text(size = 16, color = "black", face = "bold"),
          legend.text = element_text(colour="black", size = 10, face = "bold"), 
          legend.title = element_text(colour="black", size = 12, face = "bold"), 
          panel.background = element_rect(fill = "transparent")) +
    scale_x_discrete(labels=c("non-RSE","RSE")) +
    scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(0, 5, 10, 15, 20, 25, 30, 35, 40, 45, 50, 55, 60, 65, 70)) +
    scale_fill_discrete(name="Total benzodiazepine dose",labels=c("Recommended", "Low")) +
    labs(x = "Subgroup", y = "Proportion of patients (%)")

#Bar graph low non-BZD ASM dose and RSE

#Transform variable low non-BZD ASM dose into factor
class(pSERG$TOTALAEDlowSINGLEDOSE)
## [1] "numeric"
pSERG$TOTALAEDlowSINGLEDOSE <- as.factor(as.numeric(pSERG$TOTALAEDlowSINGLEDOSE))
class(pSERG$TOTALAEDlowSINGLEDOSE)
## [1] "factor"
#Transform value into percentages
percent_RSE <- pSERG %>%
    count(SE_GROUP, TOTALAEDlowSINGLEDOSE) %>%
    group_by(TOTALAEDlowSINGLEDOSE) %>%
    mutate(percent = (n / sum(n)) * 100) %>%
    ungroup()

#Create bar graph comparing non-BZD ASM dose between subgroups
percent_RSE %>%
    ggplot(aes(x = SE_GROUP, y = percent, fill = TOTALAEDlowSINGLEDOSE)) +
    geom_bar(stat = "identity", position = "dodge", width = 0.6) +
    theme(axis.text = element_text(size = 12, color = "black", face = "bold"),
          axis.title = element_text(size = 16, color = "black", face = "bold"),
          legend.text = element_text(colour="black", size = 10, face = "bold"), 
          legend.title = element_text(colour="black", size = 12, face = "bold"), 
          panel.background = element_rect(fill = "transparent")) +
    scale_x_discrete(labels=c("non-RSE","RSE")) +
    scale_y_continuous(breaks = c(0, 5, 10, 15, 20, 25, 30, 35, 40, 45, 50, 55, 60, 65, 70)) +
    scale_fill_discrete(name="First non-benzodiazepine ASM dose",labels=c("Recommended", "Low")) +
    labs(x = "Subgroup", y = "Proportion of patients (%)")

#Multivariate regression model for the probability of developing RSE and low BZD dose and non-BZD ASM dose as main predictors (RSE vs. non-RSE)

#Evaluating multicollinearity in the model using variance inflation factor (vif)
vif(glm((RSE==0)~(BZDlow10==1)+(TOTALAEDlowSINGLEDOSE==1)+ageyears+male+priorepilepsy+priorSE+STRUCTURALETIOLOGY+INTERMITTENT+BZDTIME.0+AEDTIME.0+HOMEMEDAED+HOSPITALONSET,data=pSERG, family=binomial(link='logit')))
##              BZDlow10 == 1 TOTALAEDlowSINGLEDOSE == 1 
##                   1.150662                   1.030175 
##                   ageyears                       male 
##                   1.116927                   1.039714 
##              priorepilepsy                    priorSE 
##                   1.904399                   1.224074 
##         STRUCTURALETIOLOGY               INTERMITTENT 
##                   1.030204                   1.069659 
##                  BZDTIME.0                  AEDTIME.0 
##                   1.810468                   1.872975 
##                 HOMEMEDAED              HOSPITALONSET 
##                   1.798976                   1.097616
#RSE group and low BZD and first non-BZD ASM dose as main predictors
modelf1<-glm((RSE==1)~(TOTALAEDlowSINGLEDOSE==1)+BZDlow10+ageyears+male+priorepilepsy+priorSE+STRUCTURALETIOLOGY+INTERMITTENT+BZDTIME.0+AEDTIME.0+HOMEMEDAED+HOSPITALONSET,data=pSERG, family=binomial(link='logit'))

##Multivariate regression model for the probability of developing a RSE and low or high dose group of LEV as main predictor.

#RSE group and low first AED dose without interaction term
modelf2<-glm((RSE==1)~(lowrangeLEV==1)+BZDlow10+ageyears+male+STRUCTURALETIOLOGY+BZDTIME.0+AEDTIME.0+HOMEMEDLEV,data=pSERGLEV, family=binomial(link='logit'))
summary(modelf2)

## glm(formula = (RSE == 1) ~ (lowrangeLEV == 1) + BZDlow10 + ageyears + 
##     male + STRUCTURALETIOLOGY + BZDTIME.0 + AEDTIME.0 + HOMEMEDLEV, 
##     family = binomial(link = "logit"), data = pSERGLEV)

###Multivariate regression model for the probability of receiving an low first non-BZD ASM dose

#Evaluating multicollinearity in the model using variance inflation factor (vif)
vif(glm(TOTALAEDlowSINGLEDOSE~ageyears+male+priorepilepsy+priorSE+INTERMITTENT+BZDTIME.0+AEDTIME.0+BZDlow10+HOMEMEDAED+HOSPITALONSET+STRUCTURALETIOLOGY,data=pSERG, family=binomial(link='logit')))
##           ageyears               male      priorepilepsy            priorSE 
##           1.115069           1.029379           1.899723           1.230538 
##       INTERMITTENT          BZDTIME.0          AEDTIME.0           BZDlow10 
##           1.071190           1.393591           1.400895           1.157124 
##         HOMEMEDAED      HOSPITALONSET STRUCTURALETIOLOGY 
##           1.796707           1.085231           1.034044
#Evaluate correlation between weight and age
cor(pSERG$ageyears, pSERG$WEIGHT)

#Multivariate logistic regression model - Low non-BZD ASM dose
modelf3<-glm(TOTALAEDlowSINGLEDOSE~ageyears+male+priorepilepsy+priorSE+INTERMITTENT+BZDTIME.0+AEDTIME.0+BZDlow10+HOMEMEDAED+HOSPITALONSET+STRUCTURALETIOLOGY,data=pSERG, family=binomial(link='logit'))
summary(modelf3)
